holesalers and financial representatives and selecting outside subadvisors in his experience as a portfolio manager scott introduced new tools including factor analysis valuation models quantitative ranking and comparison tools target price and position weighting analysis risk management and performance attribution he established relationships with top pension consulting firms and competed in institutional finals searches bringing in new third party assets from a national base scott’s portfolio management assignments included international equity domestic equity taxable investing and convertible securities he was twice named as one of barron’s top  mutual fund managers  just prior to joining the leuthold team scott fulfilled a lifelong career goal by serving as director of the applied investments program and teaching security analysis and other finance classes at the university of wisconsin ̶ whitewater scott received his bsba from drake university in  and an mba from the university of minnesota in  he earned his cfa designation in  and recently served on the cfa society madison board of directors latest articles activepassive return drivers july  update cotw   days ago beatlemania and narrow markets of special interest   weeks ago humble oil equity strategies   weeks ago dynamic factor investing a study in value of special interest   month ago the intelligent use of smart beta stock market   months ago stock picking in a season of animal spirits of special interest   months ago grappling with a strong us dollar outlook of special interest   months ago factor investing and the importance of market cycles of special interest   months ago active versus passive return drivers a yearend stock market   months ago an earnings bottomwhats next of special interest   months ago active vs passive return drivers cotw   months ago trends in corporate debt and coverage ratios of special interest   months ago an initial look at smart beta and factor investing of special interest 